// 🔐 secrets — proposed claims for 13-build-secrets.md. Merged only by 🔬 ledger.
// All dry-run with: uv run tools/verify_claims.py .team/proposed/secrets.jsonl
//
// Group 1 — G16 made mechanical. The repo fixture already contains everything needed to prove
// that `sensitive` masks a VALUE and not a VARIABLE; nobody had asked it the question. `-var`
// assigns the NON-sensitive `pub` the SAME string as the sensitive `sec`, and packer redacts it.
// This is the claim 13 asserted in prose but never executed. No fixture edit required.
{"id": "packer-sensitive-masks-by-value-not-variable", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["packer", "inspect", "-var", "pub=ghp_FIXTURE_SENTINEL", "tests/fixtures/packer-sensitive"], "expect": "var.pub: \"<sensitive>\"", "claim": "masking is VALUE-based, not variable-scoped: the NON-sensitive variable `pub`, assigned the sensitive variable's value via -var, also prints <sensitive>. This is why marking ssh_password=\"admin\" sensitive would redact every 'admin' in every log. Paired with CONTROL-packer-inspect-var-flag-assigns-plain-value, which proves -var really assigns and that a non-matching value prints in the clear."}
{"id": "CONTROL-packer-inspect-var-flag-assigns-plain-value", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["packer", "inspect", "-var", "pub=notthesecret_CONTROL", "tests/fixtures/packer-sensitive"], "expect": "var.pub: \"notthesecret_CONTROL\"", "claim": "CONTROL for packer-sensitive-masks-by-value-not-variable: `-var` genuinely assigns the variable, and a value that does NOT collide with the secret prints in the clear. Without this, 'pub printed <sensitive>' could be explained by inspect erroring or by -var being ignored."}
{"id": "packer-sensitive-masks-substring-inside-larger-value", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["packer", "inspect", "-var", "pub=prefix-ghp_FIXTURE_SENTINEL-suffix", "tests/fixtures/packer-sensitive"], "expect": "var.pub: \"prefix-<sensitive>-suffix\"", "claim": "redaction is SUBSTRING-level, not token-level: the secret is masked even when embedded inside a longer string. A common word marked sensitive therefore corrupts unrelated output mid-word. Shares CONTROL-packer-inspect-var-flag-assigns-plain-value."}
//
// Group 2 — the PACKER_LOG=1 pair currently cannot tell 'masking survived the debug log' from
// 'there was no debug log'. `plain_FIXTURE_CONTROL` lives on STDOUT, which is byte-identical with
// and without the overlay. These two pin the overlay's EFFECT, closing that gap.
{"id": "CONTROL-packer-log-env-overlay-is-effective", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["packer", "inspect", "tests/fixtures/packer-sensitive"], "env": {"PACKER_LOG": "1"}, "expect": "[INFO] Packer version:", "claim": "DISCRIMINATOR for packer-sensitive-hides-secret-under-debug-log: PACKER_LOG=1 genuinely produces a debug stream, and the ledger's `env` overlay genuinely reaches the subprocess. Without this, that must_fail claim is satisfied by a packer that emitted no debug log at all — its own control (CONTROL-packer-debug-log-prints-plain-literals) matches on stdout, which is unchanged by the overlay."}
{"id": "packer-debug-log-silent-when-overlay-disabled", "kind": "cli-help", "must_fail": true, "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["packer", "inspect", "tests/fixtures/packer-sensitive"], "env": {"PACKER_LOG": "0"}, "expect": "[INFO] Packer version:", "claim": "the debug stream is CAUSED by the overlay, not by the ambient environment: with PACKER_LOG=0 no [INFO] line is emitted. Pinning 0 rather than omitting the key matters because verify_claims merges env dicts and cannot UNSET a variable, so an operator exporting PACKER_LOG=1 would otherwise silently run every 'no-env' claim under debug logging. Positive control: CONTROL-packer-log-disabled-still-prints-plain-literals."}
{"id": "CONTROL-packer-log-disabled-still-prints-plain-literals", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["packer", "inspect", "tests/fixtures/packer-sensitive"], "env": {"PACKER_LOG": "0"}, "expect": "plain_FIXTURE_CONTROL", "claim": "CONTROL for packer-debug-log-silent-when-overlay-disabled, running the same argv AND the same env: under PACKER_LOG=0 packer still prints non-sensitive literals, so 'no [INFO] line' is not merely 'no output'."}
//
// Group 3 — why `use_env_var_file` must stay false, from packer's own source, pinned to the
// installed version (v1.15.4) so it cannot drift. Plain text, not HTML: developer.hashicorp.com
// renders its prose across HTML tags, so a substring grep of that page is unsound.
{"id": "packer-shell-use-env-var-file-uploads-into-guest", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["curl", "-fsSL", "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/hashicorp/packer/v1.15.4/provisioner/shell/provisioner.go"], "expect": "comm.Upload(remoteVFName", "claim": "use_env_var_file=true does not merely write a HOST tempfile: packer uploads it to the GUEST as RemoteFolder/varfile_N.sh. This is the line that makes `use_env_var_file = false` load-bearing for 13's no-write design. Pinned to tag v1.15.4, the version `packer version` reports."}
{"id": "packer-shell-guest-cleanup-is-an-unlink", "kind": "cli-help", "file": "specs/macos-ci/13-build-secrets.md", "argv": ["curl", "-fsSL", "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/hashicorp/packer/v1.15.4/provisioner/shell/provisioner.go"], "expect": "\"rm -f %s\", path", "claim": "packer's own cleanupRemoteFile unlinks the uploaded env-var file rather than shredding it. Combined with G15 (unlink does not zero blocks), packer's built-in cleanup is EXACTLY the delete-after-use antipattern 13 rejects — so use_env_var_file=true would leave the secret in the guest disk image even on a successful, non-skip_clean build."}
